description:
Let me start by saying this--in all of my 8 years of living in SF, I can count on one hand how many times I've been to Chinatown. Three times. But since Steap opened on Sacramento, right at the mouth of Waverly Street by Michelin Star awarded restaurant Mister Jiu's, I've been to China town way more times than I can even count. That's saying a lot coming from an avid coffee drinker--And yes coffee drinkers, you can grab a cup from Steap also! The decor isn't like your typical Taiwanese tea joint. It is modern, warm, and inviting with probably the cleanest restroom in Chinatown! (;
I've tried a lot of the signature drinks with my favorite being the Almond Milk Pearl and a hot Matcha Latte. Their house made boba is just the right amount of chewy and sweet. You can also make your own drink if you'd like. Most of the time I come in, tell Emil the owner what I'm in the mood for, and he'll recommend or make something on the spot that never disappoints. You can tell he's passionate and a people person! 
The baristas are welcoming, knowledgeable, and social --and the tea is really damn good. Finally, a breath of fresh air in Chinatown. I wish you all the success, one hand shaken tea at a time.
